New Records: James McCann hit two home runs and Heston Kjerstad hit one home run in the Orioles' 6-2 win over the Twins, advancing the Orioles to the playoffs.
Key Match Events: The Orioles won the series 3-0, securing their playoff spot with a 6-2 victory in the final game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was held at Target Field in Minneapolis with an attendance of 26,041 fans.
